Ahead of the conclusion of the Serie A Match-Day 22 fixtures on Monday, where Sampdoria will take on Napoli, below are the top scorers chasing the golden boot in the Italian top-flight league. Juventus forward, Cristiano Ronaldo scored twice in his side’s 3-0 victory over Fiorentina to take his tally to 19 goals this season. Lazio striker, Ciro Immobile is presently the top goal scorer in the Serie A with 25 goals. Serie A top scorers:
25 goals: Ciro Immobile (Lazio)
19 goals: Cristiano Ronaldo (Juventus)
16 goals: Romelu Lukaku (Inter Milan)
14 goals: João Pedro (Cagliari), Josip Ilicic (Atalanta)
12 goals: Luis Muriel (Atalanta)
11 goals: Lautaro Martínez (Inter Milan)
10 goals: Edin Dzeko (Roma), Francesco Caputo (Sassuolo)
9 goals: Domenico Berardi (Sassuolo), Andrea Belotti (Torino)
8 goals: Andrea Petagna, (SPAL), Andreas Cornelius (Parma)
7 goals: Arkadiusz Milik (Napoli), Robin Gosens (Atalanta), Duván Zapata (Atalanta), Felipe Caicedo (Lazio)
6 goals: Alejandro Gómez (Atalanta), Joaquín Correa (Lazio), Marco Mancosu (Lecce)